### 5. Frontend — Multi-Profile VNC Grid

#### [MODIFY] [VncViewer.tsx](file:///c:/Users/yaros/Downloads/anti/frontend/src/components/VncViewer.tsx)

- Accept `url` prop already (no change needed to the component itself — it already supports dynamic URLs)

#### [MODIFY] [VncPage.tsx](file:///c:/Users/yaros/Downloads/anti/frontend/src/tabs/vnc/VncPage.tsx)

Complete rewrite of the VNC page to support multi-profile view:

**Two modes**:
1. **Grid Mode** (default) — shows all active profile VNC streams in a responsive grid
2. **Focus Mode** — click a tile to maximize one profile's display + show logs

**Grid Mode UI**:
- Header bar with "Active Sessions" title, session count, and a "Refresh" button
- Responsive CSS grid: `grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(400px, 1fr))`
- Each tile: profile name label (top-left), VNC iframe (read-only, pointer-events-none), status indicator
- Empty state: "No active sessions — start a workflow to see browser displays"

**Focus Mode UI**:
- Full-size VNC viewer (with interactive "Take Control" button from current design)
- "Back to Grid" button
- Logs panel on the right (existing `LogsViewer`)

**Data fetching**:
- On mount: `GET /api/displays` to get initial list
- Listen to WebSocket for `display_allocated` / `display_released` events to update grid in real time
- Poll `/api/displays` every 5s as fallback

#### [NEW] [VncTile.tsx](file:///c:/Users/yaros/Downloads/anti/frontend/src/tabs/vnc/VncTile.tsx)

Small component for one grid tile:
- Profile name badge
- Embedded `<VncViewer url={...} interactive={false} />`
- Click handler → switch to focus mode
- Status dot (green = active)
- Utilitarian styling consistent with existing Logs/Monitoring pages

